-------------------------=20

Hello,=20
I don't know if many of you use Vim to write OCaml code. I had to make some=
 change on the official plugin in order to use the annotation as I wanted. =
I share my modifications in the hope that they can be useful to others : ht=
tp://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=3D3906.=20

I corrected 2 bugs and add a functionnality allowing to use annotations on =
every .ml file opened in the editor. Until now, it looks like previously an=
notation were working only on the first opened OCaml file.=20

I use my modified version without any problem for several weeks. If you try=
 my plugin, please, keep me informed of the eventual bugs.=20

Thanks=20
Pierre Vittet=

